    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1197"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1197">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">J. C. S.</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>No. 1197<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the United States Chiefs of Staff</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1197fn1">Noted by the Combined Chiefs of Staff at their
                        196th Meeting, July 19. See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_113">p. 113</ref>. Cf. <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_80">p. 80</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C. C. S.</gloss> 891/1</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-19">19 July
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Combined Chiefs of Staff Machinery After the <gloss
                            target="#t_War1">War</gloss> With Japan</hi>
                </p>
                <p>With reference to <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C. C. S.</gloss> 891,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d1197fn2">
                        <ref target="frus1945Berlinv01#d550">Document No. 550, printed in vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> the political relationship of the United States with other
                    nations in the period following this <gloss target="#t_War1">war</gloss> is not
                    yet sufficiently defined to permit the United States Chiefs of Staff to discuss
                    at this date the post-war relationships between the respective military
                    staffs.</p>
                <p>The United States Chiefs of Staff will bring up for consideration the problem of
                    the most effective military machinery to be used from now forward and prior to
                    the end of the Japanese <gloss target="#t_War1">war</gloss>.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d1197fn3">This paragraph refers to item 5, paragraph <hi
                            rend="italic">e</hi>, of the minutes of the 195th Meeting of the
                        Combined Chiefs of Staff, July 18. See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_86">pp. 86</ref>, <ref target="#pg_113">113</ref>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
